<TITLE> New BERC chief takes office </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)Sayed Yusuf Hossain has assumed office of chairman of Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission, a press release said on Monday. The Division of Energy and Mineral Resources issued a circular on his appointment on Sunday. According to the Energy Regulatory Commission Law, 2003, Hossain's tenure will be for three years. He was the comptroller and auditor general before his new job. The press release said Hossain served in many crucial positions of different ministries in his 35 years of public service. bdn
